                   "message":  "Automation hygiene (docs): fix AI_DISPATCH_AUTOMATION.md drift + mirror Rule-8 into §10.2\n\nPR-B of the 2-PR split (stacked on PR-A). Documentation-only; no script or Rust\nbehavior changes. All five doc-drift items verified against the live scripts:\n\n- §1: Codex CLI pin 0.130.x -\u003e 0.135.x; sync date 2026-05-16 -\u003e 2026-05-29\n  (the loop\u0027s timeout params post-date the old date).\n- §4: add the two undocumented root scripts Get-AiDispatchTrends.ps1 and\n  Watch-DispatchStages.ps1 to the Files \u0026 components table.\n- §6.1: the verify gate mirrors FIVE workflows (adds bench.yml,\n  cargo bench -p rge-script-bench --no-run), and powershell.yml (the 6th) is\n  explicitly NOT mirrored.\n- §8: document the three enforced loop timeouts -ModelTimeoutSec (1800),\n  -VerifyTimeoutSec (3600), -CodexStallThresholdSec (300) with their\n  ValidateRange bounds and §14.13 stall/timeout taxonomy labels.\n- §14.5: replace the false \"with no timeout\" guidance with the real internal\n  bounds while preserving the operational advice (don\u0027t wrap in a short-cap\n  runner).\n\n- PLANGATE-RULE8 (doc half): add the Protocol Rule 8 falsification paragraph to\n  the §10.2 verbatim plan-gate prompt block. It is BYTE-IDENTICAL to the\n  Invoke-AiDispatchLoop.ps1 here-string shipped in PR-A (SHA-256\n  9388229D38FEBBB43FB632377F9693C01F331945CBD7E8ECA84D1F0C0E832CBD, 765 chars),\n  keeping §10.2 a true mirror of the live orchestrator prompt.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
